Partly cloudy; observed a yellowish green cloud about 50'x100'.  Took samples.  - Kenn K.  Sample was taken to biologist at Peshtigo DNR office.  It is algae bloom with some colonizing.  It is not a blue green bloom.  - Greg Sevener- DNR Peshtigo.
68 F- sunny.  The yellowish green cloud is now about 1/3 of the lake and is washing up on the north shore.
65 F- sunny.  The yellowish green cloud is still on over 1/3 of the lake.  We have had 17-18 days of cloudy weather with 3"+ of rain.
70 F- 2" rain in last 10 days.  Still have yellowish green algae but not in tight bunches.
Water level up about 3" in June.  Over 5" rain so far.  3'-4' sizes algae still in lake.  Strong fishy smell.  Sunny- 72 F.

No rain 18 days.  Lake busy previous week of the 4th.  85 F S-W wind 5-15 mph.  Too windy to see any algae.
No rain in 23 days.  82 F.  Partly cloudy- hazy- light N breeze.  No signs of earlier algae.  Some swimmers complaining of a rash after swimming.
No sign of algae.  1 1/4 inches of rain on 7/20.  First rain in 30 days.  Still people getting "swimmers itch".
